    <section id="work">
        <h2>Our Environment Let Your Geek Shine</h2>


        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col col-lg-4">
                    <h4>HardwareTO Labs</h4>
                    <p>With a monthy or annual fees, members can reserve and use our tools, our space, and get access to our network to support the different stages of their projects.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="col col-lg-4">
                    <h4>HardwareTO Workshop</h4>
                    <p>Anyone can attend our workshop. If you are a developer, it's a great opporutnity to learn how to add your code to a physical object: We teach software folks how to build hardware stuff!</p>
                </div>
                <div class="col col-lg-4">
                    <h4>HardwareTo Meetup</h4>
                    <p>Our meetup is organized once every month to bring toronto Hardware Community Together. Speakers are invited and its a great opportunity to showcase what you are working on.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

    </section>

    <section id="equipment">
    	<h2>Our Equipments and Gadgets</h2>
    	<p>We are launching soon and we plan to equip our lab with the best gadgets in town and abroad:</p><br/>
    	<h3>Software</h3>
    	<p>Autocad, Rhino3D, Blender, 3ds Max Studio, LightWave 3D, SolidWorks, Alibre Personal Edition, Cheetah3D, bonzai3d</p><br/>
    	<h3>Hardware</h3>
    	<p>IMac machines, Cubify CubeX 3D Printer, Makerbot Replicator, Formlabs Form 1, NextEngine 3D Scanner, Otherlab Othermill</p><br/>
